article.description: Aaron Wheeler scored 20 points; Armel Potter hit the game-winning free throws with seven seconds left, and Charleston Southern beat Presbyterian 73-72 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Charleston Southern sneaks by Presbyterian, 73-72
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Aaron Wheeler scored 20 points; Armel Potter hit the game-winning free throws with seven seconds left, and Charleston Southern beat Presbyterian 73-72 on Wednesday night. The Buccaneers have won three straight in the Big South Conference, following a three-game losing streak. Wheeler hit 1 of 2 free throws to give Charleston Southern (8-11, 4-4) a 71-69 lead with 51 seconds left. Three possessions later, Presbyterian's Reggie Dillard hit a layup and was fouled by Charleston's Melvin Brooks and, after hitting the free throw, gave the Blue Hose a 72-71 lead with 15 seconds to go. However Potter was fouled by Davon Bell on the Buccaneers' final possession, setting up his game-winning free throws. Dillard had a final shot at the buzzer to win it, but missed. Potter and Patrick Wallace scored 13 apiece for Charleston Southern. DeSean Murray led Presbyterian (8-11, 3-5) with 17 points.
